        {
          "id": "cp_p02_t1",
          "elType": "widget",
          "widgetType": "text-editor",
          "settings": {
            "editor": "<p>For anglers who want to combine lodge comfort with a true wilderness experience, this program pairs Rio Manso Lodge with one of our remote river camps.</p><p>Guests begin their stay at Rio Manso Lodge, enjoying comfortable accommodations and access to some of the region's best float fisheries. Midway through the trip, we transfer you deep into Patagonia's backcountry to one of our secluded river camps. This can also be done the other way around.</p><p>Here the experience becomes more adventurous and intimate. Days are spent floating wild, untouched rivers that see very little fishing pressure, surrounded by pristine landscapes and total solitude.</p><p>Evenings are shared around camp with great food, Argentine wine, and stories from the river.</p><p>This program offers a perfect balance between comfort and wilderness exploration, and is a favorite among anglers looking for a more adventurous Patagonia experience.</p>",
            "text_color": "#6B7A8D",
